column5: Just a couple of my efforts. []
Some more quality stuff there Jack !!
You do amazing work Jack, I always enjoy looking at your carvings !!
WOW! Very nice work, Jack! Very nice!
Well done Jack ! Lots of patience required there.
Love the wood carving! I love whittling while I'm sitting round a campfire, but I just manage to turn big sticks into small slivers. Very nice work.
Once again you've done some very nice work Jack.
Nice job. As a woodworker myself, hats off to you

I was fortunate enough to see the loon carving (and Jack) over at Settler's Village this afternoon...it is definitly a great piece...  Jack and several other wood-carvers were demonstrating their craft...lots of good stuff...  Maribeth and her friend Barb were demonstrating basket weaving dressed in period costumes...
